<div class="container-fluid" id="introCard">
    <h3 class="text-justify">
        <h1 class="display-1">Welcome to Hour ISS</h1>
        <h3 class="display-3">
        Since Nov 2, 2000 human beings have had a continuous presence in space aboard the International Space Station. Much has changed in the past 16 years, both for the crew of the ISS and for we humans here on Earth. The ISS stands as one of humankind’s greatest achievements, but it is an achievement that is so far removed from the ordinary person’s day-to-day that it can fade into the background noise of modern life.<br /><br />
        We here at Intuitive Software Solutions feel that the ISS is something that we can all take part in being proud of. To that effect this site is meant to celebrate one of humanity’s most spectacular accomplishments and to try and display the contrast between what’s going on in the twittersphere and what we have high above us in the thermosphere.<br /><br />
        We hope you’ve enjoyed visiting Hour ISS
        </h3>
</div>
